                                            <p>2016-09-05</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <br>
                                    <p> A new communications strategy for Scouts Scotland has been approved by the Board. The strategy sets out to: Provide Scouts Scotland with communications that will drive and support the Scottish Strategic Plan. Improve engagement with and between members. Significantly increase awareness, perception, understanding and engagement across all non-member audiences. Maximise the use of resources available (people and financial). Provide communication support and guidance for volunteers and staff. Support Region and District teams to increase internal and external communications at a local level. An integral part of the strategy is to create a new and improved website for Scouts Scotland, which will offer a better experience for both Scout members and those interested in joining Scouting. Following member feedback from a survey that went out in the summer, work has now begun on the new website which is scheduled to launch by the end of the year – watch this space! Delivery of the communications strategy is being led by Addie Dinsmore, Head of Communications, with support from Janis McCulloch, Media and Public Affairs Officer, and Claire Simpson, Marketing and Digital Communications Officer, who joined the staff team earlier in the year.</p>
