                                    <div class="row news-head">
                                        <div class="col-sm-6 news-title">
                                            <h3>International Expedition</h3> </div>
                                        <div class="col-sm-6 news-date">
                                            <p>2016-07-22</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <br>
                                    <p>Are you heading on an international trip or expedition to Malawi, Zambia, Tanzania or South Africa next year? Then you might be entitled to apply for funding from the McConnell International Foundation. The Foundation launched the Livingstone Volunteers scheme in 2014 to support the fundraising efforts of those young Scots who have the chance to volunteer in Africa, but are struggling to meet the costs. The 2017 scheme will focus on young people aged from 15 to 19 years who have secured a place on their groups 2017 trip or expedition to sub-Saharan Eastern Africa. The grant on offer is £500 and will be a contribution to the volunteer’s own fundraising efforts. Eligibility The Livingstone Volunteer grants are offered to encourage and support those young people who would otherwise find it difficult to fund a volunteer placement in Southern Africa because of their personal and/or family circumstances. Applicants must: Be aged between 15 and 19 years old at the time of their application. Show evidence of having secured a volunteering opportunity with their Scout Group in one of the eligible countries (Malawi, Zambia, Tanzania and South Africa) Show evidence of personal challenge/difficult circumstances, i.e. be from a low-income household, have been in care or are a young carer, or live with a disability. </p>
