                                    <br>
                                    <p> We’re hosting a camp with a difference to give Cubs the chance to retake their promise to mark this year’s special Cubs 100 birthday. Join us at Loch Lomond Sea Life Aquarium on 16 December, where we’ll be setting up camp for the night, in and around the underwater tunnel. The Cubs will retake their promise before going on a VIP tour of the aquarium. There will be snacks and activities before settling down to sleep in this exciting venue. Event details Cubs are to arrive at the venue between 6pm and 6.30pm on Friday 16 December and will leave the next day between 8am and 8.30am. The cost is £35 per person for food, accommodation and activities. A £20 deposit per person is needed to book your place. How to book Groups can apply for the places up until 18 November by sending in a completed booking form and a cheque for the full amount. Places will be allocated randomly by ballot, and successful applicants will be notified by 21 November. Please note that only cheques from successful applicants will be cashed. Places will only be allocated to Groups with Leaders. We can't accept applications from individuals. Download the booking form. </p>
